<section id="To_add_the_ISO_Datastore1" remap="TID_15512">
	<title>Adding an ISO Datastore</title>
	<para>
		The following procedure adds an ISO Datastore from your <productname>Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization</productname> environment.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Add an ISO Datastore</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>PXE</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the <guilabel>ISO Datastores</guilabel> accordion.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Configuration)</guilabel>, 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1848.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject><guilabel>(Add a new ISO Datastore)</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Select the <application>Red Hat Enterprise Virtualization Manager</application> Provider hosting the ISO Datastore.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Add</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
	<formalpara>
		<title>Result:</title>
		<para>
			The ISO datastore is added to <productname>CloudForms Management Engine</productname>.
		</para>
	</formalpara>
</section>